        "last_activity_date": 1289827483,
        "creation_date": 1289819370,
        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "how can i have a list of icons in my android app;",
        "body": "<p>can any one suggest how can i have a list of icons like browser icon,email icon and contacts icon upon clicking on those it should lead to android browser,email and contacts apps respectively...right now i have done it, upon clicking buttons. Now i want icons(with image and text) instead of buttons...<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 4183721,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android",
            "eclipse"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 4183753,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 425
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c5383375813365fd284d1f4d3d6d57a7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 160478,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 380579,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/380579/xil3",
                "reputation": 16479,
                "display_name": "xil3",
                "accept_rate": 89
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1289819683,
            "creation_date": 1289819683,
            "body": "<p>Check this out:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://developer.android.com/resources/tutorials/views/hello-formstuff.html#CustomButton\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://developer.android.com/resources/tutorials/views/hello-formstuff.html#CustomButton<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>This will show you had to put the images you want in res/drawable/ and then load them up as buttons in your app.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4183753,
            "question_id": 4183721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/dEYOs.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 41275,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 119895,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/119895/macarse",
                "reputation": 93331,
                "display_name": "Macarse",
                "accept_rate": 92
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1289819731,
            "creation_date": 1289819731,
            "body": "<p>There is no widget icon.\nYou can do it yourself using a <code>LinearLayout<\/code> an <code>ImageView<\/code> and a <code>TextView<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>The xml should be something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;LinearLayout android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n  android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n  android:orientation=\"vertical\"&gt;\n\n  &lt;ImageView android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:src=\"@drawable/your_image\"/&gt;\n\n  &lt;TextView android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:text=\"@string/your_icon_text\"/&gt;\n\n&lt;/LinearLayout&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 4183763,
            "question_id": 4183721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/4aACIvDL.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 142343,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 379693,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/379693/paresh-mayani",
                "reputation": 128558,
                "display_name": "Paresh Mayani",
                "accept_rate": 95
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1289821487,
            "creation_date": 1289819713,
            "body": "<p>I thought you want to have <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ImageButton.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"> <strong><code>ImageButton<\/code><\/strong> <\/a> , clicking on that you want to open particular application/browser/contact list.<\/p>\n\n<p>ImageButton - Displays a button with an image (instead of text) that can be pressed or clicked by the user<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  &lt;ImageButton\n    android:id=\"@+id/ImageButton01\"\n    android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:src=\"@drawable/icon/&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If you wants ImageButton with Background button then set <code>android:background<\/code> attribute, as below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;ImageButton\n    android:id=\"@+id/ImageButton01\"\n    android:layout_width=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    android:src=\"@drawable/icon\"\n    android:background=\"@drawable/background_image\"/&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 4183760,
            "question_id": 4183721,
            "last_edit_date": 1289821487
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ed20598cdee3557d3cd3c4f53fe1e4be?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 237324,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 505407,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/505407/shaireen",
                "reputation": 3703,
                "display_name": "Shaireen",
                "accept_rate": 55
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1289820751,
            "creation_date": 1289819952,
            "body": "<p>You can use Android Image Button and set its property \"Clickable=true\" and do the required work on its click event listener<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4183800,
            "question_id": 4183721,
            "last_edit_date": 1289820751
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e648659dd573c1161a370efa0f5e10d6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 238127,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 506796,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/506796/tenfour04",
                "reputation": 95187,
                "display_name": "Tenfour04",
                "accept_rate": 83
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1289827483,
            "creation_date": 1289827483,
            "body": "<p>If you want an image <em>and<\/em> text in your button, the way I do it is create a 9 patch, so I can define where the text will go using the padding and stretchable areas. Then follow the same instructions as for the Custom Button already mentioned, but use a standard button, not an Image Button.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4184778,
            "question_id": 4183721
        }
